                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Porayar Dec. 4 (PTI): A 21-year-old lady teacher died on Thursday trying to save her students from drowning after their van fell into a pond in Tamil Nadus Nagapattinam district.           thi and the cleaner, Subramanian, smashed the window and came out of the van. They saved seven children. Suganthi, who did not know swimming, drowned along with nine children while trying to save them.                  
	 Keylong (PTI): The Rohtang Pass, closed for the past 25 days because of heavy snowfall, has been reopened to traffic. The snow was cleared on Thursday, facilitating traffic movement between the Kullu and Lahaul valleyes in Himachal Pradesh.                   
	 Ludhiana (PTI): Migrant labourers protesting the alleged refusal of police to register cases after their colleagues were robbed blocked a national highway in Ludhiana for hours on Thursday and set on fire several vehicles. The police fired 10 round in the air to disperse the crowd.                  
	 New Delhi: Police have arrested a hotel management graduate for allegedly morphing pictures of two air hostesses on other obscene images and circulating them on social networking sites. Jitender Singh Rana, 30, had uploaded the pictures to teach the women a lesson after failing to settle a dispute between them.                  
	 Coimbatore (PTI): A 19-year-old student who had been hit by his college bus on Wednesday succumbed to his injuries in hospital on Friday. The driver had lost control and hit Chandrasekhar, a VLB Janakiammal College student, and five of his classmates.                  
	 Srinagar (PTI): Police have arrested seven people for allegedly smuggling fuki, a rare-quality of charas, and claimed to have busted a gang of drug peddlers. The accused, including the kingpin, have been remanded in judicial custody till December 16.                                                                                                                                              
